Class MagicSquare

  • java.lang.Object
    • model.MagicSquare

  • public class MagicSquare
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is in charge of make it possible to build a magic square matrix, it requires a few variables which are going to be provided from the user.

    • Constructor Detail

      • MagicSquare

        public MagicSquare(java.lang.String startPoint,
                   java.lang.String direction,
                   int size)
        Constructor for MagicSquare class. It allows you to create a MagicSquare object. pre: the integer for size has to be an odd number. Every parameter has its correspondent type of data. post: a magic square object can be created.
        Parameters:
        startPoint - indicates which point the magic square should start to be filled in.
        direction - indicates the diagonal direction that the filling process should follow.
        size - indicates the order for the magic square, it has to be an odd number.

    • Method Detail

      • fillMagicSquare

        public void fillMagicSquare(int[] movement,
                            int[] correction,
                            int row,
                            int column)
        This method allows a MagicSquare object to fill the magicSquare integer matrix when it's created. pre: all the attributes have to be initialized and contain the correct values. post: every position in the magicSquare matrix will have its correspondent value.
        See Also:
        fillMagicSquare()

      • fillMagicSquare

        public void fillMagicSquare()
        This method gets the information from the MagicSquare object attributes and then decides the value for each needed data (as the direction and correction movement)to fill the magic square correctly. Then the gotten data is used in the overloaded method fillMagicSquare(int[], int[], int) and there is where the matrix gets filled up. post: the matrix for the requested magic square will be filled up with the correspondent values.
        See Also:
        fillMagicSquare(int[], int[], int, int)

      • correctPos

        public int[] correctPos(int row,
                        int column)
        This method evaluates 2 possible cases (-1 and magicSquare.length) for each parameter (integers) and then changes their values if it's necessary.
        Parameters:
        row - an integer for row value in magicSquare matrix.
        column - an integer for column value in magicSquare matrix.
        Returns:
        location an integer array whit length = 2, the first position has the corrected value for row, the second position has the corrected value for column.

      • magicConstant

        public int magicConstant()
        This method calculates the magic constant (result of the sum for each row, column and diagonal). post: the sum will be calculated.
        Returns:
        the result
